    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.68,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.86,
      "end": 12.48,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit libravox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 15.08,
      "end": 21.52,
      "text": "Asop's Fables. The Boy Bathing, recorded by Duncan, also known as Nerdivana.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 23.06,
      "end": 28.98,
      "text": "A boy was bathing in a river and got out of his depth and was in great danger of being drowned.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 30.2,
      "end": 35.78,
      "text": "A man who was passing along a road, heard his cries for help, and went to the riverside,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 36.02,
      "end": 42.28,
      "text": "and began to scold him for being so careless as to get into deep water, but made no attempt to help him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 43.0,
      "end": 49.34,
      "text": "Oh, sir! cried the boy. Please help me first and scold me afterwards.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 50.74,
      "end": 53.94,
      "text": "Give assistance, not advice, in a crisis.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 54.98,
      "end": 57.66,
      "text": "End of the boy bathing.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
